moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed?
How difficult have these problems made it for you to do your work, take care of things at home, or get along with people?
How often have you felt tired or low on energy over the past two weeks?
How difficult was it to concentrate on simple tasks recently?
Have you had trouble sleeping or staying asleep during the past two weeks?
How often did you feel down, depressed or hopeless?
Have you experienced a loss of appetite or overeating?
Have you had little interest or pleasure in doing things?
Do you feel like you are a failure or let your family down?
Has it been hard to do your work or take care of things at home?
In the last two weeks, have you been bothered by poor appetite?
Have you been moving around more than usual or been unusually restless?
Did you have difficulty reading the newspaper or watching TV?
Have you been bothered by trouble concentrating on things?
Have you had thoughts that you'd be better off dead?
How would you describe your level of difficulty in handling daily activities?
Do you find it difficult to get along with other people?
Have you struggled to stay focused on tasks at work or home?
How often do you feel very fidgety or restless?
How difficult was it for you to keep up with basic responsibilities?
Was the amount of food that {you/NAME} ate yesterday much more than usual, usual, or much less than usual?
When you drink tap water, what is the main source of the tap water? Is the city water supply (community water supply); a well or rain cistern; a spring; or something else?
Now I'll be asking some questions about {your/NAME's} use of table salt.
What type of salt {do you/does NAME} usually add to {your/his/her} food at the table? Would you say it is ordinary salt, sea salt, lite salt, or a salt substitute?
ORDINARY, SEA, SEASONED, OR OTHER FLAVORED SALT [includes regular iodized salt,sea salt and seasoning salts made with regular salt]
How often {do you/does NAME} add this salt to {your/his/her} food at the table? Is it rarely,occasionally, or very often?
How often is ordinary salt or sea salt added in cooking or preparing foods in your household? Is it never, rarely, occasionally, or very often?
[THIS QUESTION APPLIES ONLY TO USE OF ORDINARY SALT, SEA SALT OR SEASONED SALT AND NOT TO LITE SALT OR SALT SUBSTITUTES.]

This next question is about {your/NAME’s} use of salt at the table yesterday. Did {you/SP} add any salt to {your/her/his} food at the table yesterday? Salt includes ordinary salt, sea salt, lite salt, or a salt substitute.
What type of salt was it? (Was it ordinary salt, sea salt, lite salt, or a salt substitute?)
ORDINARY, SEA, SEASONED, OR OTHER FLAVORED SALT [includes regular iodized salt,sea salt and seasoning salts made with regular salt]
{Are you/Is NAME} currently on any kind of diet, either to lose weight or for some other health-related reason?
What kind of diet {are you/is NAME} on?[READ AS NEEDED: Is it a weight loss or low calorie diet; low fat or cholesterol diet; low salt or sodium diet; diabetic diet; or another type of diet?]
WEIGHT LOSS OR LOW CALORIE DIET
Please look at this list of fish
During the past 30 days, did you eat any types of fish listed on this card? Include any foods that had fish in them such as sandwiches, soups, or salads.
During the past 30 days, which types of fish did you eat and how many times did you eat them?

Type listed: breaded fish products, tuna (canned or fresh), bass, catfish, cod, flatfish, haddock,mackerel, perch, pike, pollock, porgy, salmon, sardines, sea bass, shark, swordfish, trout, walleye,other type of fish and unknown type of fish.
Interviewer instruction:Check each type of shellfish the SP reports eating, and then ask and record the number of times each type was eaten
Please look at this list of shellfish.
During the past 30 days, did you eat any types of shellfish listed on this card? Include any foods that had shellfish in them such as sandwiches, soups, or salads.
During the past 30 days, which types of shellfish did you eat and how many times did you eat them?
Type listed: clams, crab, crayfish (crawfish), lobster, mussels, oysters, scallops, shrimp, other shellfish (for example, octopus, squid) and unknown type of shellfish.
The next questions are about {your/SP's} recent health during the 30 days outlined on the calendar.
Did {you/SP} have a head cold or chest cold that started during those 30 days?
Did {you/SP} have a stomach or intestinal illness with vomiting or diarrhea that started during those 30 days?
Did {you/SP} have flu, pneumonia, or ear infections that started during those 30 days?
In the past 7 days, were any chemical products used in {your/his/her} home to control fleas, roaches,ants, termites, or other insects?
In the past 7 days, were any chemical products used in {your/his/her} lawn or garden to kill weeds?
CODE ‘NO’ IF THE RESPONDENT SAYS S/HE DOES NOT HAVE A LAWN OR GARDEN.

The next question is about drinking alcoholic beverages. Included are liquor (such as whiskey or gin), beer, wine,wine coolers, and any other type of alcoholic beverage. By a drink, I mean a 12 oz. beer, a 5 oz. glass of wine, orone and a half ounces of liquor
HANDCARD ALQ1 (Here are some examples of an alcoholic drink)
Considering all types of alcoholic beverages, during the past 30 days, how many times did {you/SP} have {DISPLAY NUMBER} or more drinks on an occasion?

SOFT EDIT: IF RESPONSE IS > 60 TIMES, THEN DISPLAY “YOU SAID THAT IN THE PAST 30 DAYS, YOU HAD {DISPLAY NUMBER} OR MORE DRINKS OF ANY KIND OF ALCOHOL ON AN OCCASION, (DISPLAY QUANTITY) TIMES. IS THAT CORRECT”?
The following questions ask about use of tobacco products in the past 5 days.
During the past 5 days, including today, did {you/he/she} smoke cigarettes, pipes, cigars, little cigars or cigarillos, water pipes, hookahs, or e-cigarettes?
Which of these products did {you/he/she} smoke?
Cigars, or little cigars, or cigarillos
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} smoke cigarettes?
IF R SAYS 95 OR MORE CIGARETTES PER DAY, ENTER 95.
During the past 5 days, including today, on the days {you/he/she} smoked, how many cigarettes did {you/he/she} smoke each day?
When did {you/he/she} smoke {your/his/her} last cigarette? Was it . . .
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} smoke a pipe?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} smoke cigars, or little cigars or cigarillos?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} smoke tobacco in a water pipe or Hookah?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} smoke an e-cigarette?
Smokeless tobacco products are placed in the mouth or nose and include chewing tobacco, snuff, snus, or dissolvables.
(Please do not include nicotine replacement products like patches, gum, lozenge, or spray which are considered products to help {you/him/her} stop smoking.)
During the past 5 days, including today, did {you/he/she} use any smokeless tobacco?
Which of these products did {you/he/she} use?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} use chewing tobacco, such as Redman, Levi Garrett or Beechnut?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} use snuff, such as Skoal, Skoal Bandits, or Copenhagen?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} use snus?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} use dissolvables such as strips or orbs?
During the past 5 days, including today, did {you/he/she} use any nicotine replacement therapy products such as nicotine patches, gum, lozenges, inhalers, or nasal sprays?
During the past 5 days, including today, on how many days did {you/he/she} use any nicotine replacement therapy products such as nicotine patches, gum, lozenges, inhalers, or nasal sprays?
When did {you/he/she} last use a nicotine replacement therapy product? Was it . . .
The next questions are about {your/his/her} exposure to other people’s tobacco smoke.
During the last 7 days, did {you/SP} spend time in a restaurant?
While {you were/SP was} in a restaurant, did someone else smoke cigarettes or other tobacco products indoors?
During the last 7 days, did {you/SP} ride in a car or motor vehicle?
While {you were/SP was} riding in a car or motor vehicle, did someone else smoke cigarettes or other tobacco products?
During the last 7 days, did {you/SP} spend time in a home other than {your/his/her} own?
While {you were/SP was} in a home other than {your/his/her} own, did someone else smoke cigarettes or other tobacco products indoors?
During the last 7 days, {were you/was SP} in any other indoor area?
While {you were/SP was} in the other indoor area, did someone else smoke cigarettes or other tobacco products?
The next question is about e-cigarettes.
During the last 7 days, {were you/was SP} in an indoor place where someone was using an e-cigarette, e-hookah, vape-pen or other similar electronic product?
Now I'm going to ask you some general questions about {SP's} eating habits.
Was {SP} ever breastfed or fed breastmilk?
How old was {SP} when {he/she} completely stopped breastfeeding or being fed breastmilk?
SOFT EDIT:  NUMBER CANNOT BE MORE THAN SP’S AGE.
HARD EDIT:  AGE CANNOT BE ZERO BECAUSE AGE IN MONTHS IS ALLOWED.
ENTER AGE IN DAYS, WEEKS, MONTHS OR YEARS
How old was {SP} when {he/she} was first fed formula?
How old was {SP} when {he/she} completely stopped drinking formula?

This next question is about the first thing that {SP} was given other than breast milk or formula.  Please include juice, cow’s milk, sugar water, baby food, or anything else that {SP} might have been given, even water.
How old was {SP} when {he/she} was first fed anything other than breast milk or formula?
DO NOT COUNT MEDICATIONS, VITAMIN DROPS, OR SMALL AMOUNT OF WATER THAT WAS USED FOR ORAL HYGIENE PURPOSES.
How old was {SP} when {he/she} was first fed milk?
DO NOT INCLUDE BREASTMILK OR FORMULA.

Lactaid: A modified milk product that is often consumed by individuals who have lactose intolerance. Lactaid can be purchased in various forms (i.e., 2%, skim, etc.). If respondent does not give type, probe for type (i.e., was that Lactaid regular, 2%, 1% or skim?).
Formula: A milk mixture or milk substitute that is fed to babies.
What type of milk was {SP} first fed?  Was it . . .
milk or “low-fat milk” not further specified),
Next I have some questions about {your/SP’s} eating habits.
In general, how healthy is {your/his/her} overall diet?  Would you say . . .
{Next I have some questions about {SP’s} eating habits.}
{First/Next}, I’m going to ask a few questions about milk products.  Do not include their use in cooking.

In  the  past  30  days,  how  often  did  {you/SP}  have  milk  to  drink  or  on  {your/his/her}  cereal?    Please  include  chocolate  and  other flavored milks as  well as hot cocoa made  with  milk.    Do not count small  amounts  of milk added to coffee or tea.  Would you say . . .
THIS SHOULD NOT BE A GATE QUESTION ANYMORE.

CAPI DISPLAY INSTRUCTIONS:  IF SP AGE 7-15 YEARS OLD, DISPLAY “{Next I have some questions about {SP’s} eating habits.}  First, I’m going to ask about milk products.  Do not include their use in cooking.”  IF SP AGE <= 6 OR => 16 YEARS OLD, DISPLAY “Next I’m going to ask a few questions about milk products.  Do not include their use in cooking.”
rarely – less than once a week,
sometimes – once a week or more, but less than once a day, or
often – once a day or more?
What type of milk was it?  Was it usually . . .
IF RESPONDENT CANNOT PROVIDE USUAL TYPE, CODE ALL THAT APPLY.
1% fat or low-fat milk (includes 0.5% fat milk or “low-fat milk” not further specified), .
The next question is about regular milk use.
A regular milk drinker is someone who uses any type of milk at least 5 times a week.  Using this definition, which statement best describes {you/SP}?
{I've/He's/She's} been a regular milk drinker for most or all of {my/his/her}  life, including {my/his/her} childhood.
{I've/He's/She's} never been a regular milk drinker.
{my/his/her} life – sometimes {I've/he's/she's} been a regular milk drinker and sometimes {I have/he has/she has} not been a regular milk drinker.
Now, I’m going to ask you how often {you/SP} drank milk at different times in {your/his/her} life.
How often did {you/SP} drink any type of milk, including milk added to cereal, when {you were/s/he was} . . .
IF NECESSARY, PROBE FOR USUAL OR MOST COMMON AMOUNT FOR THIS TIME PERIOD.
THESE (A-C) SHOULD NOT BE GATE QUESTIONS ANYMORE.
rarely – less than once a week,
a. a child between the ages of 5 and 12 years old?  Would you say. . .
sometimes – once a week or more, but less than once a day, or
often – once a day or more?
b. a teenager between the ages of 13 and 17 years old?  Would you say . .

c. a young adult between the ages of 18 and 35 years old?  Would you 
say . . .
The next questions are about meals provided by community or government programs.
In  the  past  12  months,  did  {you/SP}  receive  any  meals  delivered  to  {your/his/her}  home  from  community  programs, “Meals on Wheels”, or any other programs?
In the past 12 months, did {you/SP} go to a community program or senior center to eat prepared meals?
During the school year, {do you/does SP} attend a kindergarten, grade school, junior or high school?
INTERVIEWER INSTRUCTION:  ENTER ‘NO’ IF THE SP IS HOME SCHOOLED.
Does {your/SP's} school serve school lunches?  These are complete lunches that cost the same every day.
During the school year, about how many times a week {do you/does SP} usually get a complete school lunch?
{Do you/Does SP} get these lunches free, at a reduced price, or {do you/does he/she} pay full price?
Does {your/SP's} school serve a complete breakfast that costs the same every day?
During the school year, about how many times a week {do you/does SP} usually get a complete breakfast at school?
{Do you/Does SP} get these breakfasts free, at a reduced price, or {do you/does he/she} pay full price?
{Do you/Does SP} get a free or reduced price meal at any summer program {you/he/she} attends?
Next are a few questions about the WIC program.
Has {SP} ever received benefits from WIC, that is, the Women, Infants, and Children program?

WIC:  WIC is short for the Special Supplemental Food Program for Women, Infants, and Children. This program provides  food  assistance  and  nutritional  screening  to  low-income  pregnant  and  postpartum  women  and  their  infants, as well as to low-income children up to age 5.
Is {SP} now receiving benefits from the WIC program?
Did {SP} receive benefits from WIC when {he/she} was less than one year old?

Did {SP} receive benefits from WIC when {he/she} {was/is} between the ages of {1 to {SP AGE/4} years old/12 to 
{SP AGE} months old}?
If SP age = 1, DISPLAY “12 to {the current age of the SP in months} months old”;
If SP age = 2 or 3, DISPLAY “1 to {the current age of the SP in years} years old”;
If SP age >3, DISPLAY “1 to 4 years old”.
How long {did SP receive/has SP been receiving} benefits from the WIC program?
IF FSQ.673 = 1, DISPLAY HAS SP BEEN RECEIVING
Did {SP’s} mother receive benefits from WIC, while she was pregnant with {SP}?
How many months pregnant was {SP’s} mother when she began to receive WIC benefits?

Next I’m going to ask you about meals.  By meal, I mean breakfast, lunch and dinner.  During the past 7 days, how many meals {did you/did SP} get that were prepared away from home in places such as restaurants, fast food places, food stands, grocery stores, or from vending machines?

{Please  do  not  include  meals  provided  as  part  of  the  school  lunch  or  school  breakfast./Please  do  not  include  
meals provided as part of the community programs you reported earlier.}
IF DBQ381G = 1 OR DBQ.411G = 1, DISPLAY {Please do not include meals provided as part of the school lunch or school breakfast.}
IF DBQ.301 = 1 OR DBQ.330 = 1, DISPLAY {Please do not include meals provided as part of the community programs you reported earlier.}
How many of those meals {did you/did SP} get from a fast-food or pizza place?
NUMBER OF MEALS ENTERED IN DBQ.900 MUST BE EQUAL TO OR LESS THAN NUMBER ENTERED IN DBQ.895.  IF NOT, DISPLAY THE FOLLOWING:
“THE NUMBER OF MEALS FROM A FAST FOOD OR PIZZA PLACE CANNOT BE GREATER THAN NUMBER OF MEALS PREPARED AWAY FROM HOME.”
Some  grocery  stores  sell  “ready  to  eat”  foods  such  as  salads,  soups,  chicken,  sandwiches  and  cooked  vegetables in their salad bars and deli counters.
During the past 30 days, how often did {you/SP} eat “ready to eat” foods from the grocery store?  Please do not include sliced meat or cheese you buy for sandwiches and frozen or canned foods.
SOFT EDIT IF RESPONSE IS GREATER THAN 6 TIMES A DAY. “THIS IS AN UNUSUALLY LARGE NUMBER OF TIMES PER DAY, PLEASE VERIFY THE ANSWER.”
During the past 30 days, how often did {you/SP} eat frozen meals or frozen pizzas?  Here are some examples of frozen meals and frozen pizzas.
Next I’m going to ask a few questions about the nutritional guidelines recommended for Americans by the federal government.
{Have you/Has SP} heard of My Plate?
{Have you/Has SP} looked up the My Plate plan on the internet?
{Have you/Has SP} tried to follow the recommendations in the My Plate plan?
{Are you/Is SP} the person who does most of the planning or preparing of meals in {your/SP’s} family?
INTERVIEWER INSTRUCTION:  IF SP ANSWERS “SOMETIMES” OR “50/50”, ENTER YES.
{Do you/Does SP} share in the planning or preparing of meals with someone else?
{Are you/Is SP} the person who does most of the shopping for food in {your/SP’s} family?
{Do you/Does SP} share in the shopping for food with someone else?
